This scheme describes terms that specify the facing of planar geologic features (eg, upright, overturned), as defined by the IUGS Commission for Geoscience Information (CGI) Geoscience Terminology Working Group. By extension, this vocabulary includes all concepts in this conceptScheme, as well as concepts in any previous versions of the scheme.

This file contains the 2017 SKOS-RDF version of the CGI Planar Polarity Code vocabulary. Vocabulary Shepherd: Ollie Raymond. Compilation and review in Google doc spreadsheet, converted to MS Excel for SKOS generation using SKOS_for_GA_from_XLS_2016.03.xslt
